internal.EndGame: Boolean variable indicating if the game must be ended
internal.RepeatSequence: Boolean, if True the robot should repeat the current sequence
internal.UserSpeed: The speed of the user in repeating the sequence

external.NumRepetitions: Number of times a sequence has been provided, up to a maximum of 3
external.SequenceSet: Boolean, if True a sequence has been set
external.ResponseTimerActive: Boolean, if True the robot is waiting for the user to respond
external.UserResponded: Boolean, if True the user has responded with a sequence
external.UserResponseTime: The time taken by the user to respond, in seconds
external.LatestUserAccuracy: A measure of how well the user did in their last sequence attempt
external.LatestUserSpeed: A measure of how fast the user was in their last sequence attempt, taking into account sequence difficulty
external.AttemptedReengageUser: Boolean, if True the robot attempted to reengage the user after a timeout
external.NumSequences: Number of sequences that have been provided, up to a maximum of 3
external.UserAttention: The level of attention the user is paying to the task
external.UserFrustration: The level of frustration the user is experiencing
external.UserConfusion: The level of confusion the user is experiencing
